title: Prep Roundup: Live Oak JV football opens league with win
text:
Live Oak Acorns Posted: Monday, October 5, 2015 9:26 am 
Greg Sperry ran back a game-clinching touchdown as the Live Oak junior varsity took down Leigh 20-13 Friday night. 
The Acorns trailed 7-0 at the half, before getting on the board in the third quarter. 
Despite giving up a touchdown in the fourth, Live Oak went up 14-13 when Sperry took back a kick 98 yards for the final sore. 
He then pulled down an interception to clinch the win. 
Live Oak improves to 3-1 overall and 1-0 in league play. Sobrato downs Oak Grove in 5-game thriller 
Ellie Downing had a season-high 19 kills as Sobrato edged out Oak Grove in five games 20-25, 25-10, 25-17, 17-25, 15-10. 
The Bulldogs even their league mark at 2-2 with the win Thursday. 
This was Downingâ€™s best match since scoring 12 kills against Wilcox in two games. 
She was joined by Kennedie Schilling who scored 13 kills and Stephanie Cloughesy with eight. 
Schilling also had a big night defensively, pulling out 28 digs. Anya Weislak followed with 22. 
Sobrato will next host Pioneer 6 p.m. Tuesday.
